  <!-- The Questionnaire -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 data-en="The Questions" data-es="Las Preguntas">The Questions</h2>
        <p data-en="Ten questions. Same for every candidate. Designed to put candidates on record about specific policies, not platitudes." data-es="Diez preguntas. Las mismas para cada candidato. Diseñadas para que los candidatos se posicionen sobre políticas específicas, no platitudes.">
          Ten questions. Same for every candidate. Designed to put candidates on record about specific policies, not platitudes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="questions-list">
        <div class="question-category" data-en="HOUSING & AFFORDABILITY" data-es="VIVIENDA Y ASEQUIBILIDAD">HOUSING & AFFORDABILITY</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Rent Stabilization" data-es="Estabilización de Alquileres">Rent Stabilization</h3>
            <p data-en="Colorado currently preempts cities from enacting rent control. Do you support Denver passing rent stabilization if the state enables it? What annual cap on rent increases would you support? If the state does not act, what specific steps would you take at the city level to protect tenants from displacement?" data-es="Colorado actualmente impide que las ciudades implementen control de alquileres. ¿Apoya que Denver apruebe estabilización de alquileres si el estado lo permite? ¿Qué tope anual de aumentos de alquiler apoyaría? Si el estado no actúa, ¿qué pasos específicos tomaría a nivel municipal para proteger a los inquilinos del desplazamiento?">
              Colorado currently preempts cities from enacting rent control. <strong>Do you support Denver passing rent stabilization if the state enables it? What annual cap on rent increases would you support?</strong> If the state does not act, what specific steps would you take at the city level to protect tenants from displacement?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Homelessness & Encampment Policy" data-es="Personas sin Hogar y Política de Campamentos">Homelessness & Encampment Policy</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver City Council passed a moratorium on encampment sweeps during freezing temperatures; Mayor Johnston vetoed it. Would you vote to override that veto? Do you support a housing-first approach over enforcement-based sweeps? What is your plan for reducing unsheltered homelessness in your district?" data-es="El Concejo Municipal de Denver aprobó una moratoria sobre desalojos de campamentos durante temperaturas bajo cero; el Alcalde Johnston la vetó. ¿Votaría para anular ese veto? ¿Apoya un enfoque de vivienda primero sobre desalojos basados en la aplicación de la ley? ¿Cuál es su plan para reducir la falta de vivienda sin refugio en su distrito?">
              Denver City Council passed a moratorium on encampment sweeps during freezing temperatures; Mayor Johnston vetoed it. <strong>Would you vote to override that veto? Do you support a housing-first approach over enforcement-based sweeps?</strong> What is your plan for reducing unsheltered homelessness in your district?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="PUBLIC SAFETY" data-es="SEGURIDAD PÚBLICA">PUBLIC SAFETY</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="STAR & LEAD Expansion" data-es="Expansión de STAR y LEAD">STAR & LEAD Expansion</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver's STAR program sends mental health professionals instead of police to crisis calls (10,000+ calls, zero incidents requiring police backup). The LEAD program diverts people facing low-level charges to case management instead of arrest (Seattle evaluation: 58% lower recidivism). Do you support expanding both programs to 24/7 citywide coverage? Should community members be able to make LEAD referrals directly, without requiring police contact?" data-es="El programa STAR de Denver envía profesionales de salud mental en lugar de policía a llamadas de crisis (más de 10,000 llamadas, cero incidentes que requirieron respaldo policial). El programa LEAD desvía a personas que enfrentan cargos menores a gestión de casos en lugar de arresto (evaluación de Seattle: 58% menor reincidencia). ¿Apoya expandir ambos programas a cobertura 24/7 en toda la ciudad? ¿Deberían los miembros de la comunidad poder hacer referencias a LEAD directamente, sin requerir contacto policial?">
              Denver's STAR program sends mental health professionals instead of police to crisis calls (10,000+ calls, zero incidents requiring police backup). The LEAD program diverts people facing low-level charges to case management instead of arrest (Seattle evaluation: 58% lower recidivism). <strong>Do you support expanding both programs to 24/7 citywide coverage? Should community members be able to make LEAD referrals directly, without requiring police contact?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Police Budget Reallocation" data-es="Reasignación del Presupuesto Policial">Police Budget Reallocation</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver For All proposes a phased reallocation of the police budget: Phase 1 (~8% / $25M) expands STAR and LEAD citywide; Phase 2 (~15% / $45M) adds violence intervention and substance treatment; Phase 3 (~25% / $75M) adds youth services, restorative justice, and housing. Each phase evaluated before the next begins. What level of reallocation do you support? Where would you direct the funds?" data-es="Denver Para Todos propone una reasignación gradual del presupuesto policial: Fase 1 (~8% / $25M) expande STAR y LEAD a toda la ciudad; Fase 2 (~15% / $45M) agrega intervención de violencia y tratamiento de sustancias; Fase 3 (~25% / $75M) agrega servicios juveniles, justicia restaurativa y vivienda. Cada fase se evalúa antes de comenzar la siguiente. ¿Qué nivel de reasignación apoya? ¿A dónde dirigiría los fondos?">
              Denver For All proposes a phased reallocation of the police budget: Phase 1 (~8% / $25M) expands STAR and LEAD citywide; Phase 2 (~15% / $45M) adds violence intervention and substance treatment; Phase 3 (~25% / $75M) adds youth services, restorative justice, and housing. Each phase evaluated before the next begins. <strong>What level of reallocation do you support? Where would you direct the funds?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="ECONOMIC JUSTICE" data-es="JUSTICIA ECONÓMICA">ECONOMIC JUSTICE</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Living Wage" data-es="Salario Digno">Living Wage</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver's minimum wage is $18.81/hour. A single adult with one child needs $27.35/hour to meet basic expenses in Denver (MIT Living Wage Calculator). Do you support raising Denver's minimum wage to $25/hour, indexed to cost of living? Do you support eliminating the tipped worker subminimum wage (One Fair Wage)?" data-es="El salario mínimo de Denver es $18.81/hora. Un adulto soltero con un hijo necesita $27.35/hora para cubrir gastos básicos en Denver (Calculadora de Salario Digno del MIT). ¿Apoya aumentar el salario mínimo de Denver a $25/hora, indexado al costo de vida? ¿Apoya eliminar el salario mínimo reducido para trabajadores que reciben propinas (Un Salario Justo)?">
              Denver's minimum wage is $18.81/hour. A single adult with one child needs $27.35/hour to meet basic expenses in Denver (MIT Living Wage Calculator). <strong>Do you support raising Denver's minimum wage to $25/hour, indexed to cost of living? Do you support eliminating the tipped worker subminimum wage (One Fair Wage)?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="QUALITY OF LIFE & INFRASTRUCTURE" data-es="CALIDAD DE VIDA E INFRAESTRUCTURA">QUALITY OF LIFE & INFRASTRUCTURE</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">6</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Municipal Broadband" data-es="Banda Ancha Municipal">Municipal Broadband</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver voters approved municipal broadband in 2020, but the city has not built it. Meanwhile, Comcast and CenturyLink charge some of the highest internet prices in the country, and 15% of Denver households lack broadband access. Do you support Denver building city-owned fiber internet infrastructure? What timeline would you push for?" data-es="Los votantes de Denver aprobaron la banda ancha municipal en 2020, pero la ciudad no la ha construido. Mientras tanto, Comcast y CenturyLink cobran algunos de los precios de internet más altos del país, y el 15% de los hogares de Denver carecen de acceso a banda ancha. ¿Apoya que Denver construya infraestructura de internet de fibra óptica propiedad de la ciudad? ¿Qué plazo impulsaría?">
              Denver voters approved municipal broadband in 2020, but the city has not built it. Meanwhile, Comcast and CenturyLink charge some of the highest internet prices in the country, and 15% of Denver households lack broadband access. <strong>Do you support Denver building city-owned fiber internet infrastructure? What timeline would you push for?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">7</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Disability Rights & Inclusion" data-es="Derechos de las Personas con Discapacidad e Inclusión">Disability Rights & Inclusion</h3>
            <p data-en="Over 70,000 Denver residents live with a disability. People with disabilities make up a third to half of all people killed by police nationally. Less than 5% of Denver's housing stock is wheelchair accessible. The Commission for People with Disabilities is advisory-only with no enforcement power. What specific commitments would you make for disabled constituents? Do you support elevating the Commission from advisory to enforcement authority?" data-es="Más de 70,000 residentes de Denver viven con una discapacidad. Las personas con discapacidad representan de un tercio a la mitad de todas las personas asesinadas por la policía a nivel nacional. Menos del 5% de las viviendas de Denver son accesibles para sillas de ruedas. La Comisión para Personas con Discapacidades es solo consultiva, sin poder de aplicación. ¿Qué compromisos específicos haría para los electores con discapacidades? ¿Apoya elevar la Comisión de consultiva a autoridad con poder de aplicación?">
              Over 70,000 Denver residents live with a disability. People with disabilities make up a third to half of all people killed by police nationally. Less than 5% of Denver's housing stock is wheelchair accessible. The Commission for People with Disabilities is advisory-only with no enforcement power. <strong>What specific commitments would you make for disabled constituents? Do you support elevating the Commission from advisory to enforcement authority?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="DEMOCRACY & ACCOUNTABILITY" data-es="DEMOCRACIA Y RENDICIÓN DE CUENTAS">DEMOCRACY & ACCOUNTABILITY</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">8</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Flock Cameras & Surveillance" data-es="Cámaras Flock y Vigilancia">Flock Cameras & Surveillance</h3>
            <p data-en="Denver City Council voted 12-0 to reject the Flock ALPR camera contract. Mayor Johnston bypassed the vote by structuring a contract just under the $500K council approval threshold. Audit logs revealed ICE searched Denver's camera data 1,400+ times. Do you support the mayor's authority to override council on surveillance contracts? Should council approval be required before any surveillance technology is deployed?" data-es="El Concejo Municipal de Denver votó 12-0 para rechazar el contrato de cámaras ALPR de Flock. El Alcalde Johnston evadió la votación estructurando un contrato justo por debajo del umbral de $500K que requiere aprobación del concejo. Los registros de auditoría revelaron que ICE buscó los datos de las cámaras de Denver más de 1,400 veces. ¿Apoya la autoridad del alcalde para anular al concejo en contratos de vigilancia? ¿Debería requerirse la aprobación del concejo antes de implementar cualquier tecnología de vigilancia?">
              Denver City Council voted 12-0 to reject the Flock ALPR camera contract. Mayor Johnston bypassed the vote by structuring a contract just under the $500K council approval threshold. Audit logs revealed ICE searched Denver's camera data 1,400+ times. <strong>Do you support the mayor's authority to override council on surveillance contracts? Should council approval be required before any surveillance technology is deployed?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">9</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Participatory Budgeting" data-es="Presupuesto Participativo">Participatory Budgeting</h3>
            <p data-en="Cities like Paris, New York, and Porto Alegre let residents directly decide how to spend portions of the public budget. Denver has no participatory budgeting program. Should Denver residents directly decide how to spend a portion of the city budget? What dollar amount would you allocate to resident-directed spending?" data-es="Ciudades como París, Nueva York y Porto Alegre permiten que los residentes decidan directamente cómo gastar porciones del presupuesto público. Denver no tiene un programa de presupuesto participativo. ¿Deberían los residentes de Denver decidir directamente cómo gastar una porción del presupuesto de la ciudad? ¿Qué cantidad en dólares asignaría al gasto dirigido por los residentes?">
              Cities like Paris, New York, and Porto Alegre let residents directly decide how to spend portions of the public budget. Denver has no participatory budgeting program. <strong>Should Denver residents directly decide how to spend a portion of the city budget? What dollar amount would you allocate to resident-directed spending?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="question-category" data-en="OPEN-ENDED" data-es="PREGUNTA ABIERTA">OPEN-ENDED</div>

        <div class="question-card">
          <span class="question-number">10</span>
          <div>
            <h3 data-en="Your District's Top Priority" data-es="La Prioridad Principal de Su Distrito">Your District's Top Priority</h3>
            <p data-en="What is the single most important issue facing your district, and what specific policy would you propose to address it? Be specific: name the problem, name the solution, name how you'd pay for it." data-es="¿Cuál es el problema más importante que enfrenta su distrito y qué política específica propondría para abordarlo? Sea específico: nombre el problema, nombre la solución, nombre cómo lo financiaría.">
              <strong>What is the single most important issue facing your district, and what specific policy would you propose to address it?</strong> Be specific: name the problem, name the solution, name how you'd pay for it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

